 by the \"system firmware\", rather than the \"hardware\"."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1854,"reviewer":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davepacheco"},"message":"Done"},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1857,"reviewer":{"name":"Jordan Hendricks","email":"jordan.hendricks@joyent.com","username":"jordanhendricks"},"message":"Is there an example in which `manta-adm` might show the hardware configuration? I\u0027m not sure I\u0027ve ever seen it in its output."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1857,"reviewer":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davepacheco"},"message":"I don\u0027t believe it has an option to list the hardware type nor the service processor IP.  I\u0027m not sure why that text was added, and if it\u0027s more confusing, I can strip it out as part of this ticket as well."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1857,"reviewer":{"name":"Jordan Hendricks","email":"jordan.hendricks@joyent.com","username":"jordanhendricks"},"message":"I don\u0027t find it confusing. As a reader, I\u0027m just curious if it\u0027s relevant to me, and how I could find it if I need to."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1857,"reviewer":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davepacheco"},"message":"Looking over it more closely, I found this and the bit about the SP IP too much of a non-sequitur, so I\u0027ve rewritten this to remove it.  (This section is about locating servers and about the properties that `manta-adm cn` can show.  The bit about unique identifiers is just background.  The hardware type has nothing to do with locating systems, \"manta-adm cn\", or unique identifiers; and the SP IP is not supported by any of the tooling and is pretty much outside the scope of the product at this point.)"},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1857,"reviewer":{"name":"Jordan Hendricks","email":"jordan.hendricks@joyent.com","username":"jordanhendricks"},"message":"Sounds good. Thanks for explaining."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1868,"reviewer":{"name":"Joshua M. Clulow","email":"jmc@joyent.com","username":"jclulow"},"message":"I would be inclined to capitalise this as \"IDs\", as you are for \"CNs\"."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1868,"reviewer":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davepacheco"},"message":"Done"},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1897,"reviewer":{"name":"Joshua M. Clulow","email":"jmc@joyent.com","username":"jclulow"},"message":"Perhaps mention, or include an example of, finding just the zones for a particular service?"},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1897,"reviewer":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davepacheco"},"message":"I spent some time trying to incorporate this, but it feels like the specific examples belong in the manual page (and there is one there), and I didn\u0027t want to have it duplicated here, so I\u0027ve just added some detail to the subsequent paragraph.  Let me know how that sounds.\n\nI believe many of these sections predate the \"manta-adm\" manual page.  Longer-term, the better answer here is probably to have all of the context and examples in manual pages.  Then this section of the operator guide can just be a brief index of tasks and tools.  A separate Manta Operator Tutorial wouldn\u0027t be a bad idea."},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","line":1897,"reviewer":{"name":"Joshua M. Clulow","email":"jmc@joyent.com","username":"jclulow"},"message":"That\u0027s great -- thanks!"}],"files":[{"file":"/COMMIT_MSG","type":"ADDED","insertions":7,"deletions":0},{"file":"docs/operator-guide.md","type":"MODIFIED","insertions":43,"deletions":-35}],"sizeInsertions":43,"sizeDeletions":-35},{"number":"2","revision":"9c24be65a82f0dfd82fe16e5a52bb0459ee928e0","parents":["1022c9627a94c3dca64278641b38176518b1deea"],"ref":"refs/changes/53/2753/2","uploader":{"name":"David Pacheco","email":"dap@joyent.com","username":"davep